programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about a mentally unstable news anchor who, after being told he's to be fired, becomes a media superstar when he begins delivering nightly rants and threatens an on-air suicide for his final broadcast. Paddy Chayevsky's script won an Oscar for Best Original Screenplay; Peter Firth received a posthumous Best Actor award as the unhinged newsman; and Faye Dunaway won Best Actress as a scheming network exec. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Paper Chase
programme.desc: The tribulations of first-year law students at Harvard, specifically a brilliant but naive young man who, as with most of his fellow aspiring attorneys, is in fearful awe of a demanding, ego-deflating professor (John Houseman, who won a Best Supporting Actor Oscar and reprised the role in the TV series adapted from the film). (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Breaking Away
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about four teens coming of age in an Indiana college town, where one of them has a passion for bicycle racing. Screenwriter Steve Tesich won an Oscar. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Brian's Song
programme.desc: A look at the special relationship between Gale Sayers and Brian Piccolo, both star players for the Chicago Bears. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cinderella Liberty
programme.desc: About the bittersweet relationship between a sailor and a cynical prostitute, complicated by her illegitimate son. Filmed in Seattle. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Soldier in the Rain
programme.desc: Unlikely Army sergeant pals -- one content, one ambitious -- run into trouble when a pretty teen's boyfriend resents how the men are poaching his gal away. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Command
programme.desc: Based on a real story, the film recounts the 2000 K-141 Kursk submarine disaster. It tells the story of the Russian nuclear submarine as it's sinking to the bottom of the Barents Sea and the sailors fighting to survive in it. Officer Mikhail Kalekow is part of the crew that is still alive and waiting for their rescue. However, the rescue mission seems hindered by politics and bureaucracy among Russia, France, Norway and Britain. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Morituri
programme.desc: In this WWII spy story, a German deserter is coerced by a British Intelligence officer to impersonate a Gestapo official in order to get aboard a German blockade runner that is carrying a valuable rubber cargo from the Orient. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Wild River
programme.desc: Elia Kazan's study of individualism vs. progress in the early days of the Tennessee Valley Authority. Montgomery Clift, Lee Remick, Jo Van Fleet. Hamilton: Jay C. Flippen. Bailey: Albert Salmi. Betty: Barbara Loden. Cal: James Westerfield. Clark: Frank Overton. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Born to Be Bad
programme.desc: A manipulative gold digger sets her sights on a wealthy man who's already engaged, ignoring the advances of a rugged writer who loves her despite her flaws. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: They Drive by Night
programme.desc: Two driven brothers who own a trucking business deal with crooked distributors and unscrupulous rivals while establishing their transport company, and one battles through a crippling injury and the other is victimized by a mentally unstable woman. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: On Dangerous Ground
programme.desc: A hardened police officer agrees to help the sister of a killer when she realizes the victim's father hopes to get revenge by murdering the perpetrator, who is deeply mentally ill. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: High Sierra
programme.desc: Humphrey Bogart shot his way to bankable stardom with this caper drama about a self-destructive ex-con who's "just rushing toward death" after an attempted heist of a California luxury resort goes South and a woman complicates his flight from the law. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Bigamist
programme.desc: The dilemma of a traveling salesman (Edmond O'Brien) with a wife in San Francisco---and another in Los Angeles. Joan Fontaine, Ida Lupino. Good cast and direction overcome the soap-opera plot. Lupino also directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Trapped
programme.desc: Film noir in which Treasury agents tap a convicted criminal to help them capture a counterfeiting gang. The convict meets up with his girlfriend and seeks to get back in business. Unbeknownst to him, his every move is being monitored. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Angel Face
programme.desc: An ambulance driver becomes ensnared in the dangerous charm and deadly scheme of a sensuous beauty who is utterly obsessed with murdering her stepmother. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Cornered
programme.desc: A World War II veteran hunts down the Nazi collaborators who killed his wife. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Knock on Any Door
programme.desc: Engrossing study of a juvenile delinquent on trial for murder. Humphrey Bogart, John Derek. Kerman: George Macready. Adele: Susan Perry. Emma: Allene Roberts. Vito: Mickey Knox. Drake: Barry Kelley. Nelly: Cara Williams. Directed by Nicholas Ray. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: I Died a Thousand Times
programme.desc: An aging bank robber is released from prison. He decides to pull one last robbery at a high-class mountain resort before retiring, and use some of the loot to pay for a young girl's surgery. Unfortunately the crime doesn't go as planned... (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The Hitch-hiker
programme.desc: Two men on a fishing trip are menaced by a killer who is full of hatred due to abuse he suffered as a child. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Private Property
programme.desc: Two degenerates prey on a frustrated housewife in Southern California, with tragic results.(n)

programme.title: Pardon Us
programme.desc: Laurel and Hardy's first feature film. Stan and Ollie land in jail, driving their captors daft. Wilfred Lucas, Walter Long, Jimmy Finlayson. James Parrott directed. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Blackboard Jungle
programme.desc: An early film study of teens gone wild chronicles the efforts of an idealistic and dedicated teacher trying to cope with his classroom full of incorrigibles, including knife-wielding punks, in an urban high school. The film launched Bill Haley & the Comets' rock-and-roll anthem "Rock Around the Clock." (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Capone
programme.desc: Melodrama with Ben Gazzara as the Prohibition-era Chicago crime boss. Susan Blakely, Harry Guardino, John Cassavetes, Sylvester Stallone. Jake: Peter Maloney. Big Jim: Frank Campanella. Anton: Royal Dano. Joe: Dick Miller. Hymie: John David Chandler. Dion: John Orchard. Giuseppe: Mario Gallo. Sam: Tom Cook. Joseph: Russ Martin. Directed by Steve Carver. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: The FBI Story
programme.desc: The story of the FBI is told from the perspective of one agent as he investigates such nefarious groups as gangsters, Nazis, Cold War spies, and the Klu Klux Klan. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Get Carter
programme.desc: A ruthless hood suspects his brother's supposedly accidental death was no accident, and sniffs out the trail of lies and deceit with bloody consequences. (Repeat).(n)

programme.title: Dog Day Afternoon
programme.desc: A bank robbery in Brooklyn goes wrong and evolves into a protracted hostage situation, turning the plan's mastermind into a media celebrity and the event into a media circus. Based on a true story. (Repeat).(n)
